oai_dc:dc.dc:title: An economic assessment of twin births in British dairy herds
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Eddy, R. G.
Davies, O.
David, C.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: twinning
reproductive performance
health
production
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The effect of twinning on the subsequent health, production and reproductive performance of dairy cattle was studied by analysing the data derived from 19,755 calvings which occurred during three years on 37 farms. Full article published in Veterinary Record (1991) 129, 526-529
